│ ### Root Cause Analysis ###                                                   │
│                                                                               │
│ -------------------- BEGIN --------------------                               │
│ 1. Understanding the Issue:                                                   │
│ The transformation in SimplifyDemandedUseFPClass for llvm.copysign under a    │
│ demanded FP-class mask that excludes positive classes rewrites the call by    │
│ setting the sign operand to a constant (e.g., -1.0 for forcing negative or    │
│ +0.0 for forcing positive/zero). This is used as a roundabout way to model    │
│ fneg(fabs(x)) or fabs(x). However, this changes the sign bit of NaNs as well. │
│ In the provided reproducer, the source returns a signaling NaN with a         │
│ positive sign bit, while the target returns a signaling NaN with a negative   │
│ sign bit. Although both are NaNs, the bit pattern differs, and Alive2         │
│ correctly flags this as an incorrect transformation.                          │
│                                                                               │
│ Key point: copysign on a NaN returns a NaN with the sign of the second        │
│ operand. Replacing the sign operand with a constant alters the nan's sign     │
│ even when the demanded FP-class doesn't care about sign for NaN. InstCombine  │
│ must preserve exact semantics (bit pattern) for NaNs unless we can prove NaN  │
│ is impossible.                                                                │
│                                                                               │
│ 2. Analyzing opt's Log:                                                       │
│ - First transformation occurs in InstCombinerImpl::SimplifyDemandedUseFPClass │
│ at the copysign intrinsic handling.                                           │
│ - The log shows: after visiting ret, it adds a deferred replacement: set      │
│ operand 1 of copysign to -1.0 because (DemandedMask & fcPositive) == fcNone.  │
│ Then it folds to fabs + fneg.                                                 │
│ - This modification directly leads to different NaN sign in the target        │
│ (negative) compared to source (positive from %unknown.sign = +0.0), as shown  │
│ by Alive2.                                                                    │
│                                                                               │
│ 3. Root Cause Analysis:                                                       │
│ The transformation assumes it's safe to force the sign of the result when the │
│ demanded mask excludes positive classes. However, copysign propagates the     │
│ sign to NaNs as well. Changing the sign operand changes the exact value for   │
│ NaNs. Because the function's nofpclass attribute excludes only positive       │
│ finite classes (pinf, pzero, psub, pnorm) but allows NaNs, the demanded mask  │
│ does not rule out NaNs. Therefore, the replacement is not                     │
│ semantics-preserving when the first operand may be NaN.                       │
│                                                                               │
│ We must restrict the transform to cases where we can prove the first operand  │
│ cannot be NaN (i.e., Known info indicates NaN is impossible), otherwise we    │
│ cannot change the sign operand to a constant.                                 │
│                                                                               │
│ 4. Proposed Edit Point(s):                                                    │
│ - File: llvm/lib/Transforms/InstCombine/InstCombineSimplifyDemanded.cpp       │
│ - Lines: 2014-2026                                                            │
│ - Change: Gate the two "roundabout" replacements for copysign under a check   │
│ that the first operand is known not-NaN. Compute Known for operand 0 and only │
│ proceed if NaN is known impossible.                                           │
│                                                                               │
│ Suggested patch (conceptual):                                                 │
│                                                                               │
│ Replace:                                                                      │
│   if ((DemandedMask & fcPositive) == fcNone) {                                │
│     // Roundabout way of replacing with fneg(fabs)                            │
│     I->setOperand(1, ConstantFP::get(VTy, -1.0));                             │
│     return I;                                                                 │
│   }                                                                           │
│                                                                               │
│   if ((DemandedMask & fcNegative) == fcNone) {                                │
│     // Roundabout way of replacing with fabs                                  │
│     I->setOperand(1, ConstantFP::getZero(VTy));                               │
│     return I;                                                                 │
│   }                                                                           │
│                                                                               │
│ With:                                                                         │
│   // Only safe to force sign when the input cannot be NaN, because changing   │
│   // the sign operand changes the sign bit of NaNs (affecting bit pattern).   │
│   KnownFPClass KnownX = computeKnownFPClass(I->getOperand(0), fcAllFlags,     │
│ CxtI, Depth + 1);                                                             │
│                                                                               │
│   if (KnownX.isKnownNever(fcNan)) {                                           │
│     if ((DemandedMask & fcPositive) == fcNone) {                              │
│       // Replace with fneg(fabs) by forcing sign negative                     │
│       I->setOperand(1, ConstantFP::get(VTy, -1.0));                           │
│       return I;                                                               │
│     }                                                                         │
│     if ((DemandedMask & fcNegative) == fcNone) {                              │
│       // Replace with fabs by forcing sign from +0.0                          │
│       I->setOperand(1, ConstantFP::getZero(VTy));                             │
│       return I;                                                               │
│     }                                                                         │
│   }                                                                           │
│                                                                               │
│ This ensures we only alter the sign operand when x is proven non-NaN.         │
│                                                                               │
│ 5. Conclusion:                                                                │
│ The incorrect transformation stems from forcing the sign in copysign under    │
│ demanded FP-class constraints without accounting for NaN preservation. By     │
│ guarding the replacement with a check that the first operand is known         │
│ not-NaN, we avoid changing the bit pattern of NaNs and preserve correctness.  │
│ This fix prevents the fabs/fneg rewrite when NaN is possible, eliminating the │
│ mismatch observed by Alive2 while still allowing the optimization when safe.  │
│ --------------------  END  --------------------                               │
